<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Ventura County Service</p>
    <h2>Ventura County is affluent, suburban, and underserved by most appliance companies</h2>
    <div class="body-text"><p>Ventura County doesn't always get the same service coverage as LA County or Orange County, despite having one of the highest median household incomes in California. Thousand Oaks and Westlake Village have a concentration of luxury appliances — Sub-Zero, Wolf, Thermador, Viking — that many appliance repair companies either can't service or won't travel to service.</p>
        <p>Our Thousand Oaks branch at (424) 208-0228 is dedicated to Ventura County. This isn't a Los Angeles technician driving an hour to reach you — it's a branch that operates specifically in this market. Same day appliance repair in Ventura County is our core offering here, not an afterthought.</p>
        <p>The county's housing stock is predominantly single-family suburban — Thousand Oaks and Newbury Park built heavily through the 1980s and 1990s, Camarillo with a mix of older and newer construction, Simi Valley with large family homes. Significant Whirlpool and GE in older stock, Samsung and LG in newer. And in Westlake Village and Hidden Hills, full Sub-Zero and Wolf kitchens are common.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

