        <h2>Ventura County's climate varies more than people expect</h2>
        <p>Thousand Oaks and Westlake Village sit in a transition zone between LA County's heat and the coastal marine layer from the Pacific. Summer afternoons hit 95°F+, but mornings stay cool. This temperature swing stresses refrigeration seals and compressors differently than a steady coastal or inland environment.</p>
        <p>The Camarillo area has a strong coastal marine influence — Oxnard and Ventura see salt air effects similar to Santa Monica. Oak Park and Hidden Hills have the dust and dry heat of the interior. Our technicians who work Ventura County know these climate zones and factor them in on every service call.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="context-facts">
        <div class="cfact"><h4>🏡 High luxury density (Westlake, Thousand Oaks)</h4><p>Westlake Village and Hidden Hills have Sub-Zero, Wolf, and Thermador comparable to Beverly Hills. OEM parts in stock.</p></div>
        <div class="cfact"><h4>🌡️ Afternoon heat + cool mornings</h4><p>Temperature swings stress compressors and seals differently than steady heat. Our Ventura County techs know this pattern.</p></div>
        <div class="cfact"><h4>🌊 Coastal marine (Ventura, Camarillo, Oxnard)</h4><p>Salt air affects appliances within a few miles of the coast. Same 4–6 month maintenance protocol as Santa Monica.</p></div>
        <div class="cfact"><h4>🏢 Dedicated Thousand Oaks branch</h4><p>(424) 208-0228 is a dedicated Ventura County number — not LA dispatch. Faster same-day response across the county.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
