      <div class="repair-card"><span class="rtag">Thousand Oaks</span><h3>"Samsung ice maker jammed — water leaking inside fridge"</h3><p>Samsung French door with frozen ice maker assembly from defrost failure. Defrosted, replaced defrost sensor, confirmed ice maker cycling correctly. Fixed same afternoon.</p></div>
      <div class="repair-card"><span class="rtag">Camarillo</span><h3>"Washing machine shaking violently during spin"</h3><p>LG front-load — shipping bolts had never been removed at installation three years ago. Vibration had also loosened the drum bearing. Both fixed. First time the machine ran correctly.</p></div>
      <div class="repair-card"><span class="rtag">Simi Valley</span><h3>"Oven temperature running 50°F low — Thanksgiving disaster"</h3><p>GE wall oven with failed bake element. Replaced element, recalibrated temperature sensor, tested with thermometer before leaving — accurate within 5°F.</p></div>
